oms and can have lunch together (not included). \nYou will then explore old Bukhara with your guide. The old town is a largely coherent structure in which one mosque follows another, in which one encounters Koranic schools, madrassas and mausoleums at every turn and in which the ruins of the old city fortress are impressive. The city is easy to explore on foot, as the distances are not far and there are many atmospheric street cafes that invite you to linger. \nThe oasis city in the Kisilkum Desert was once legendarily rich and one of the most important junctions on the Silk Road. However, Bukhara's history as one of the oldest cities and center of Islam in Central Asia goes back even further. Blue is the first color of the city, because the domes and magnificent facades of the madrassas and mosques glow blue. The old town is intact despite the Soviet era, and oriental life takes a leisurely course here... \nThose who like to travel on their own also have the opportunity to discover this fascinating city today - or you can use it tomorrow morning. \nLunch and dinner not included. \nOvernight stay in an oriental bed and breakfast guesthouse in twin rooms.\nMeals: Breakfast at the hotel.\n	\N
